            "created_at": "2019-03-10T16:27:46Z",
            "updated_at": "2019-03-10T16:27:46Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just to add here, since this thread helped me, the `app.jinja_env.auto_reload = True` made it work for me again. \r\n\r\nTo summarize for posterity: if you touch the Jinja2 environment in any way before the `app.run` call (e.g. adding a filter), you will need the line above before `app.run` for your templates to be auto-reloaded after changes. This is at least what I've observed. \r\n\r\nThanks to folks here on the resolution, saved me some trouble. \ud83d\ude3a "
